%N A396777 Decimal expansion of log(2)^2/2.
%D A396777 Ovidiu Furdui, Limits, Series, and Fractional Part Integrals: Problems in Mathematical Analysis, New York: Springer, 2013. See Problem 3.14, pages 141, 164 and 174.
%H A396777 Michael I. Shamos, <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220206102634/https://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.366.9997&amp;rep=rep1&amp;type=pdf">A catalog of the real numbers</a>, 2011. See pp. 304-305.
%H A396777 Anthony Sofo and Amrik Singh Nimbran, <a href="https://doi.org/10.3390/math7090833">Euler Sums and Integral Connections</a>, Mathematics, Vol. 7, No. 9 (2019), Article 833. See p. 7.
%H A396777 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-02462-8">(Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer International Publishing, 2019, p. 112, eq. (3.84), and p. 499.
%H A396777 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%H A396777 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A396777 Equals A253191 / 2.
%F A396777 Equals Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^(k+1) * H(k)/(k+1), where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number.
%F A396777 Equals Sum_{k>=2} H(k-1)/(k * 2^k).
%F A396777 Equals Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^(k+1) / (k^2 * 2^k * binomial(2*k,k)).
%F A396777 Equals Integral_{x=0..1} log(x+1)/(x+1) dx = Integral_{x=1..2} log(x)/x dx.
%F A396777 Equals -Integral_{x>=0} log(x)/(exp(x)+1) dx.
%F A396777 Equals -(Li_2(1/2) + Li_2(-1)) = zeta(2)/2 - Li_2(1/2) = A072691 - A076788.
%F A396777 Equals lim_{n->oo} A348063(n)/n!.
%F A396777 Equals Sum_{k>=1} (AH(k)-log(2))/k, where AH(k) = A058313(k)/A058312(k) is the k-th alternating harmonic (or skew-harmonic) number (Furdui, 2013).
